cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.GR, cs.MM

The paper proposes a deep learning approach for remote sensing image synthesis, specifically for generating a high-resolution synthetic spectral band using low-resolution and existing high-resolution bands. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories. The use of remote sensing data and the focus on spectral bands suggest the information retrieval (cs.IR) category as well. The proposed approach also involves image stitching, which falls under the graphics (cs.GR) category. Finally, the paper discusses a real-world application of the synthesized band, which could potentially fall under the multimedia (cs.MM) category.
